annotationA: Peptidyl-prolyl cis-trans isomerase; PPIases accelerate the folding of proteins. It catalyzes the cis-trans isomerization of proline imidic peptide bonds in oligopeptides; Belongs to the cyclophilin-type PPIase family. PPIase A subfamily
annotationB: 60S ribosomal protein L4; Structural constituent of ribosome. It is involved in the biological process described with: centrosome duplication; translation; Belongs to the universal ribosomal protein uL4 family
